wikipedia_page.main: Mohamed Alie Sesay (born 2 August 1994) is a professional footballer who plays as a defender or defensive midfielder for Indonesian club Persebaya Surabaya. Born in England, he represents the Sierra Leone national team.

response: *15 May 2013 – Alie Sesay and Callum Elder sign new deals.

Two days following victory at Carlisle, Sam Walker signed a permanent 18-month contract with the club. The January transfer window also saw the departure of youth-team graduate Freddie Ladapo, who left for Conference club Kidderminster Harriers. Colchester additionally signed Leicester City under-21 captain Alie Sesay on loan until the end of the season to provide cover for Magnus Okuonghae and Tom Eastman.
*11 July 2014 – Alie Sesay signs a one-year contract extension until the summer of 2015.

On 14 January, Alie Sesay joined Zira on an 18-month contract.

On 29 January, Zira announced the departure of Alie Sesay by mutual consent, with Filipe Pachtmann joining the next day on loan from Lviv until the end of the season, with an option to make the move permanent on a three-year contract at the end of the season.
On 31 January, Sabail announced the signing of Alie Sesay on a contract until the end of the season.
